The paper deals with the agreement algorithm for multiagent systems, which is a topic in the field of control systems (cs.SY) and multiagent systems (cs.MA). The paper also considers time-varying topology and communication delays, which are common issues in distributed computing (cs.DC) and networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes criteria for achieving consensus, which involves decision-making and optimization, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
